<p>U.S. President Donald Trump said the United States will keep &quot;massive&quot; tariffs on Indian goods unless New Delhi stops importing Russian oil, adding that Prime Minister Narendra Modi told him India would end such purchases; he made the remarks aboard Air Force One on October 19 [reuters.com#1][thehindu.com#1][scmp.com#1]. India’s foreign ministry responded that it was not aware of any conversation between the leaders that day [reuters.com#1]. The U.S. position is that Russian petroleum revenue funds the war in Ukraine [reuters.com#1][dawn.com#1]. India has emerged as the biggest buyer of seaborne Russian crude since 2022 [reuters.com#1].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/MaYne6WbRrLk40TSLJh__cwguE7xdXYhE-bSKDuqwCWafcXibS0Qu5YBCjvnQiunPNy-F-m-M2KjkgbHJuj5F5jP5HqcQd4fbl4448uvlYQT94ujQwXydJQ8rMu6EmXQkuun_8TNZlcPIfuNLdR2jlNZvsHfvlGktTFxiTj9W4iZQ6X78Gp-t9aJVu9DGCIcB-N_44o77OR-ODq9cbbgVj84hlpT6ZL7PE5ejS_CvC3Nu_HJz9ABCoIEhDVntcbzlFJvXhnNYmcOgcpg' alt='President Trump and Prime Minister Modi pictured in a mirror during a joint press conference at the White House, February 13, 2025 (file photo).' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Tariff structure: Russian oil purchases have been a key irritant in prolonged U.S.-India trade talks, with half of a 50% tariff package on Indian goods linked to those purchases [reuters.com#1][dawn.com#1].</li><li>Purchase levels: A White House official said India has halved its purchases of Russian oil, though this has been contested by Indian sources citing current buying patterns [reuters.com#1][dawn.com#1].</li><li>Consumer priority: India’s foreign ministry said New Delhi’s main concern is to safeguard the interests of the Indian consumer [reuters.com#1].</li><li>Import timing: Indian sources reported refiners have already placed orders for November loadings, so any reductions may only appear in December–January import data [dawn.com#1].</li></ul><blockquote>I spoke with Prime Minister Modi of India, and he said he&#x27;s not going to be doing the Russian oil thing - President Donald Trump</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>President Trump: He reiterated that tariffs will remain unless India ends Russian oil imports and said Modi assured him purchases would stop. (<a href='https://www.reuters.com/world/india/trump-vows-keep-massive-tariffs-india-until-russian-oil-imports-cease-2025-10-20/'>Reuters</a>)</li><li>India’s Ministry of External Affairs: It said it was not aware of any telephone conversation that day and emphasized protecting consumers’ interests. (<a href='https://www.reuters.com/world/india/trump-vows-keep-massive-tariffs-india-until-russian-oil-imports-cease-2025-10-20/'>Reuters</a>)</li><li>Indian sources: They indicated there had been no immediate reduction in Russian oil purchases given orders already placed for upcoming loadings. (<a href='https://www.dawn.com/news/1950131/trump-vows-to-keep-massive-tariffs-on-india-until-russian-oil-imports-cease'>Dawn</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.scmp.com/news/asia/south-asia/article/3329609/trump-warns-india-massive-tariffs-will-remain-unless-it-ends-russian-oil-imports'>End Russian oil imports or ‘massive’ tariffs will remain, Trump warns India</a> - scmp.com</li><li><a href='https://michaelwest.com.au/trump-uses-massive-tariffs-to-pressure-india/'>Trump uses ‘massive’ tariffs to pressure India</a> - michaelwest.com.au</li><li><a href='https://www.reddit.com/r/worldnews/comments/1ob9fsq/trump_says_india_to_pay_massive_tariffs_until/'>Trump says India to pay ‘massive’ tariffs until Russian oil imports cease, says spoke to Modi: ‘He’s not going to be doing…’</a> - reddit.com</li><li><a href='https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/trump-says-india-to-pay-massive-tariffs-if-it-continues-to-buy-russian-oil/article70184546.ece'>Trump says India to pay ‘massive tariffs’ if it continues to buy Russian oil</a> - thehindu.com</li><li><a href='https://www.reuters.com/world/india/trump-vows-keep-massive-ta